# Harbor — CODEOWNERS (Foundation F5: Anti-Goodhart Tamper Guards).
#
# These paths define the guardrails an agent must not weaken to "go green":
# the executable invariants, the check definitions, the pinned toolchain, the
# CI outer loop, the frozen golden vectors, the PII allow-list, and the north
# star. Requiring review on them means weakening a check is an EXPLICIT, human-
# reviewed act — never a quiet side effect of making a build pass.
#
# NOTE: `@harbor/maintainers` is a placeholder — set it to the real owning
# team/handles for this org before relying on branch protection.

# The executable invariants registry (§A.8/§11.7 → tests).
/invariants/                    @harbor/maintainers

# The check definitions themselves (a weakened check is invisible if unreviewed).
/Makefile                       @harbor/maintainers

# The pinned, hermetic toolchain (F3) — changing pins changes every verdict.
/flake.nix                      @harbor/maintainers
/flake.lock                     @harbor/maintainers

# The agent-readable outer loop (F7) — CI is the loop an agent can't skip.
/.github/                       @harbor/maintainers

# Check tooling + linters (agent-check, piifields, testweakening).
/tools/                         @harbor/maintainers

# Frozen crypto golden vectors (F2) — a change here is a crypto-output change.
**/testdata/*vectors*.json      @harbor/maintainers

# The deny-by-default PII allow-list (F10).
/internal/telemetry/            @harbor/maintainers

# The north star — a design change is explicit, never smuggled.
/docs/DESIGN.md                 @harbor/maintainers
